org.jcvi.jillion.trace.fastq

Interface FastqRecordVisitor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFastqRecordVisitor

    public interface FastqRecordVisitor
    FastqRecordVisitor is a visitor interface to visit a single fastq record inside of a fastq file.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Method Detail

      • visitNucleotides

        void visitNucleotides(String nucleotides)
        Visit the nucleotide sequence of the current fastq record as a String.
        Parameters:
        nucleotides - the NucleotideSequence; will never be null.

      • visitEncodedQualities

        void visitEncodedQualities(String encodedQualities)
        Visit the encoded quality values for the current fastq record. If the fastq file breaks the quality values across multiple lines, then encodedQualities will be the concatenation of all of those lines with all whitespace removed. This method will not be called if visitQualities(QualitySequence) is used instead.
        Parameters:
        encodedQualities - the encoded quality values as a single line string; will never be null.
        See Also:
        FastqQualityCodec

      • visitQualities

        void visitQualities(QualitySequence qualities)
        Visit the the actual quality values (not encodedc) for the current fastq record. This method will only be called if the fastq implementation does not encode the quality values. This method is only called on specific fastq formatted files (for example MAQ encoded bfq files) and method will only be called in visitEncodedQualities(String) is NOT called.
        Parameters:
        qualities - the actual non-encoded quality values; will never be null.
        See Also:
        visitEncodedQualities(String)

      • visitEnd

        void visitEnd()
        Visit the end of the current fastq record.

      • halted

        void halted()
        The parser has stopped parsing the current fastq record due to FastqVisitorCallback#haltParsing() being called. The end of the fastq record was not yet reached.
